    <div id="main">
     <p>
      <img height="146" src="/images/main/home_image.jpg" width="400"/>
      <img alt="You make the news, we help you let the world know about it" height="146" src="/images/main/home_text.jpg" width="300"/>
     </p>
     <div class="col23_divided">
      <div class="column23">
       <h3>
        Telling the world about the news at UCR
       </h3>
       <p>
        The News &amp; Information team of the University Communications department is here to get the word out to the media and the world about UC Riverside’s research, programs, and people.
       </p>
       <p>
        The News and Information team services to the UCR community include press releases, fielding media inquiries, and facilitating faculty and staff media interactions and editorial page placements. The team generates a daily email regarding media highlights, and works closely with our colleagues on the University Communications marketing team developing news-related social media and visual content.
       </p>
       <h3>
        Experts on Demand
       </h3>
       <p>
        UCR has many qualified experts on demand to provide insight or comment on a particular field. Visit our
        <a href="https://mediasources.ucr.edu/" title="Experts on Demand">
         Experts on Demand page
        </a>
        for view a list of experts by name or department.
       </p>
       <p>
        To read the campus news generated by the team, please
        <a href="https://ucrtoday.ucr.edu/" title="UCR Today">
         visit UCR Today.
        </a>
       </p>
       <h3>
        In The News
       </h3>
       <p>
        Read the latest about UC Riverside in the media with UCR In The News. Subscribe by sending an email to
        <a href="mailto:news@ucr.edu?subject=Subscribe%20to%20News">
         news@ucr.edu
        </a>
        .
       </p>
       <br/>
       <a href="http://mediarelations.ucr.edu/news.html">
        View our latest news releases.
       </a>
       <div>
       </div>
       <div class="clear section_h">
       </div>
       <div class="">
        <h3 class="notop">
         <img alt="UCR Magazine" class="img_R_borderless" height="175" src="/images/ucr_magazine.png" style="float: left;" width="120"/>
        </h3>
        <h3 class="notop" style="margin-left: 180px;">
        </h3>
        <h3 class="notop" style="margin-left: 150px;">
         <img alt="UCR Magazine Quarterly Publication" height="35" src="/images/title_ucr_magazine.jpg" style="float: left;" width="132"/>
        </h3>
        <p style="margin-left: 150px;">
        </p>
        <p style="margin-left: 150px;">
         Published quarterly,
         <a href="http://magazine.ucr.edu">
          UCR Magazine
         </a>
         keeps readers informed about the important academic pursuits and research contributions that affect our community, state, nation and world. It also helps keep our alumni abreast of each other's accomplishments. UCR Magazine can also be
         <a href="http://magazine.ucr.edu">
          accessed online
         </a>
         .
        </p>
       </div>
       <div class="clear section_h">
       </div>
       <div class="">
        <h3 class="notop">
         <img alt="InsideUCR" class="img_R_borderless" height="191" src="/images/insideucr.png" style="float: left;" width="121"/>
        </h3>
        <h3 class="notop" style="margin-left: 150px;">
         <img alt="InsideUCR Bi-Monthly Publication" height="34" src="/images/title_insideucr.jpg" style="float: left;" width="135"/>
        </h3>
        <p>
        </p>
        <p style="margin-left: 150px;">
         <a href="http://ucrtoday.ucr.edu/inside-ucr">
          InsideUCR
         </a>
         is a bi-monthly newsletter for the UC Riverside faculty and staff. It is delivered via campus email to UCR employees and is also available electronically from the
         <a href="http://ucrtoday.ucr.edu/inside-ucr">
          InsideUCR
         </a>
         website. Have an idea for a story?
         <a href="mailto:news@ucr.edu">
          Contact us!
         </a>
        </p>
       </div>
      </div>
